# Frontmatter & Links

The schema and link style are defined in `docs/vault-contract.md` (sections 3,
4, 6). This rule states the discipline.

## Frontmatter

- Every generated note carries the contract's keys, in the contract's order,
  including `generated_by: p2v` (the ownership marker). Unused optional fields
  are omitted, never `null`.
- `tags` always begins with `pdf-import` and the source slug. Inferred topic
  tags (enriched tier) are appended, never substituted.
- Use the deterministic writer in `scripts/lib/frontmatter.py`; do not hand-emit
  YAML with a different key order or quoting.

## Enrichment (enriched tier, `/p2v-enrich-document`)

- Enrichment is **inferred, labeled, additive, and outside the determinism
  guarantee**. It adds an optional one-line `summary` (a faithful condensation of
  the note's own body — fabrication ban) and appended `topic/*` + `enriched`
  tags; it never edits `source`/pages/structure.
- Write enrichment ONLY through `scripts/apply_enrichment.py` (which wraps the
  deterministic writer and enforces safe-write) — never hand-edit the YAML.
- Topic tags come from the library-scoped controlled vocabulary
  (`topic-tags.json`), so they stay consistent across books.

## Content repair (tier-neutral, `/p2v-repair-document`)

- Structural repair of a malformed table or glued index is a separate,
  tier-neutral skill — it edits the body, not frontmatter, and adds no inferred
  content, so a repaired note keeps its current tier.
- A body repair is allowed only when a deterministic guard proves the edit is
  layout-only: write it through `scripts/apply_repair.py` (which enforces
  safe-write, runs `table_guard.data_drift_strict` / `index_guard.data_drift`,
  and for tables also asserts non-table prose is byte-identical). A failing edit
  is refused and flagged, never applied. `verify_table.py --strict` /
  `verify_index.py` run the same guards standalone for previewing.

## Wikilinks (the consistency twin)

- Internal links are **vault-relative and aliased**:
  `[[<source-slug>/<path>/<number>-<slug>|<display title>]]`.
- **Bare links are forbidden** (`[[basename]]`) — they break when basenames
  repeat. The only permitted bare target is the root `index`.
- `prev`/`next` walk the ordered leaf sequence; `parent` points to the enclosing
  folder note (or the library index, for the per-PDF MOC). Folder-note MOCs omit
  `prev`/`next`.

## Library index

- The vault-root `index.md` is co-owned: only the region between
  `<!-- p2v:auto-start -->` and `<!-- p2v:auto-end -->` is rewritten. Preserve
  everything else.

## Forbidden

- Bare or unaliased internal wikilinks.
- Reordering/renaming frontmatter keys, or omitting `generated_by`.
- Rewriting anything outside the library index managed region.
